1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.xyz Support Admin)

2
00:00:06,560 --> 00:00:08,400
(Somkid Agriculture 18-8-8)

3
00:00:11,920 --> 00:00:14,440
I’m going to marry this woman.

4
00:00:22,200 --> 00:00:25,960
I’ll renew the land lease
for S Mall for another 30 years

5
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:28,240
if I get to marry this woman.

6
00:01:16,520 --> 00:01:17,720
P’Si

7
00:01:18,920 --> 00:01:21,800
Me? Marry you? Are you serious?

8
00:01:21,800 --> 00:01:23,720
Just because you won’t renew the land lease

9
00:01:23,720 --> 00:01:26,480
and it might shut down my family’s mall,

10
00:01:26,520 --> 00:01:29,680
doesn’t mean we’re totally doomed, okay?

11
00:01:29,680 --> 00:01:30,720
Fine.

12
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:34,479
If you change your mind, feel free to call me.

13
00:01:34,520 --> 00:01:36,360
I’ll get going.

14
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:12,440
If we can settle this land lease issue,

15
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:14,520
your dad and I were thinking...

16
00:06:15,200 --> 00:06:17,160
maybe it’s time we finally step back.

17
00:06:17,880 --> 00:06:19,760
Is something wrong with Dad?

18
00:06:20,400 --> 00:06:22,240
Why would he say that all of a sudden?

19
00:06:22,720 --> 00:06:24,800
Well... I’m not really sure either.

20
00:06:24,840 --> 00:06:28,080
That’s his decision, dear. I’m not involved.

21
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:29,360
It’s nothing, sweetheart.

22
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:30,960
I just want some rest.

23
00:06:31,640 --> 00:06:33,040
I was thinking...

24
00:06:33,520 --> 00:06:36,960
I’ll take your mom on that
round-the-world honeymoon I promised.

25
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:39,560
We’ve been through a lot, haven’t we?

26
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:43,320
Song, one more thing.

27
00:06:43,320 --> 00:06:47,200
I want you to take over as CEO at the company.

28
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:50,920
What?

29
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:53,200
What did you just say, Dad?

30
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:55,920
Say that again so I can hear it too.

31
00:06:57,400 --> 00:06:58,640
Oh, you’re awake?

32
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:01,840
Why are you sleeping your life away like that?

33
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:03,080
Excuse me?

34
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:05,040
Sleeping your life away?

35
00:07:05,040 --> 00:07:09,200
I woke up at six and got
all dressed up this pretty, okay?

36
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:12,440
And you’re still saying
I’ve been lazing around?

37
00:07:13,520 --> 00:07:14,600
Of course.

38
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:16,920
You’re just the unloved child.

39
00:07:16,920 --> 00:07:18,600
Not the favorite like Song here.

40
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:20,480
Everything she does is perfect.

41
00:07:20,520 --> 00:07:23,880
Hey, what’s with this
favorite vs. unfavorite nonsense?

42
00:07:24,240 --> 00:07:27,240
And hello? It’s six in the evening.

43
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:29,120
Not six in the morning.

44
00:07:29,440 --> 00:07:30,960
Six p.m.

45
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:33,080
Six p.m.

46
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:35,040
If that’s not called sleeping your life away,

47
00:07:35,080 --> 00:07:36,440
then what is?

48
00:07:37,640 --> 00:07:38,760
I don’t care.

49
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:40,960
I’m not accepting this.

50
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:43,400
Why does Song get to be the CEO?

51
00:07:43,400 --> 00:07:44,960
I’m the older one.

52
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:47,280
Why does she get to jump ahead of me?

53
00:07:47,320 --> 00:07:48,480
I’m the big sister.

54
00:07:48,520 --> 00:07:51,720
But you’ve never really succeeded
at anything, have you?

55
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:53,880
Have you ever solved a company problem

56
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:55,960
like Song has?

57
00:07:57,120 --> 00:07:59,040
You never even gave me a chance.

58
00:07:59,120 --> 00:08:00,840
You only ever gave Song chances.

59
00:08:01,400 --> 00:08:03,760
If you wanted to know
the problem, why didn’t you ask?

60
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:06,240
And do you even know who the landowner is?

61
00:08:06,280 --> 00:08:09,040
They’re not renewing the lease for our mall.

62
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:18,000
You didn’t even tell me, Dad.

63
00:08:18,120 --> 00:08:19,480
If you had told me,

64
00:08:19,520 --> 00:08:22,400
I could’ve handled everything for you.

65
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:25,160
Just eat, Si.

66
00:08:25,520 --> 00:08:28,440
You’re rambling. You’ll upset your dad.

67
00:08:28,720 --> 00:08:30,080
Okay?

68
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:32,880
No. I’m not eating.

69
00:08:32,919 --> 00:08:34,360
I’m not hungry anymore.

70
00:08:34,400 --> 00:08:35,640
Song,

71
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:38,039
let’s talk about this again tomorrow, alright?

72
00:08:38,120 --> 00:08:39,480
Pass me the salad.

73
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:40,520
Yes, Dad.

74
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:42,159
One,

75
00:08:42,520 --> 00:08:44,440
two, yum.

76
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:59,600
Tomorrow at one in the afternoon,

77
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:01,160
we’re meeting Klao, right?

78
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:03,360
Then call a meeting with
all the teams in the morning.

79
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:05,960
I want to see what
new offers we can present.

80
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:07,040
Yes, Dad.

81
00:09:18,920 --> 00:09:21,040
Your bag and the car are ready, Miss Si.

82
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:23,240
Thank you, Auntie.

83
00:09:23,240 --> 00:09:26,760
You’re the only one in this house
who actually cares about me.

84
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:30,440
Where are you heading today, Miss Si?

85
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:33,240
Shopping.

86
00:09:48,680 --> 00:09:50,640
(S MALL)

87
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:19,360
Daddy, I’ll come work at
our mall with you someday, okay?

88
00:10:19,520 --> 00:10:22,000
My little angel, my Si.

89
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:23,520
Why would you need to work?

90
00:10:23,560 --> 00:10:25,240
We have plenty of staff already.

91
00:10:25,280 --> 00:10:28,720
You just stay pretty and be Daddy’s princess.

92
00:10:28,720 --> 00:10:30,960
Come on, princess, put on your crown.

93
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:35,280
You know princesses don’t work, right?

94
00:10:35,280 --> 00:10:37,000
Just be a good girl,

95
00:10:37,040 --> 00:10:39,200
and make Mom and Dad happy.
That’s all you need to do.

96
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:41,080
Just be a good girl?

97
00:10:41,120 --> 00:10:42,480
That’s right.

98
00:10:42,520 --> 00:10:44,600
We have plenty of money, sweetheart.

99
00:10:44,640 --> 00:10:46,400
You don’t need to work at all.

100
00:10:46,400 --> 00:10:48,040
Yay!

101
00:10:48,320 --> 00:10:49,600
Si doesn’t need to work.

102
00:10:49,640 --> 00:10:52,960
Si will be Mom and Dad’s princess forever.

103
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:57,440
So pretty...

104
00:11:21,800 --> 00:11:23,120
Hey bro...

105
00:11:23,720 --> 00:11:25,840
Why are you home so late today?

106
00:11:25,920 --> 00:11:28,080
Stopped by Uncle Somkid’s to buy fertilizer.

107
00:11:28,120 --> 00:11:30,160
Got a bunch of free shirts too.

108
00:11:30,320 --> 00:11:31,760
Jiw, take some.

109
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:33,880
Nice, thanks bro!

110
00:11:36,480 --> 00:11:37,840
Missed you.

111
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,760
I’ll take these two, bro.

112
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:46,080
These are bold as hell, totally my vibe.

113
00:11:46,120 --> 00:11:47,400
Thanks, bro.

114
00:11:47,440 --> 00:11:50,960
Now I’ve got something cool
to wear to the hospital tomorrow.

115
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:53,080
By the way...

116
00:11:53,120 --> 00:11:55,280
why do you like wearing fertilizer shirts?

117
00:11:55,280 --> 00:11:57,160
You’ve got tons of nice, stylish clothes.

118
00:11:57,160 --> 00:11:58,400
Why don’t you wear those?

119
00:11:58,400 --> 00:12:01,360
They were free, why wouldn’t I wear them?

120
00:12:01,400 --> 00:12:03,400
Whether you’re rich or broke,

121
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:05,680
people don’t judge you by your clothes, Jiw.

122
00:12:05,720 --> 00:12:07,600
Plenty of people have
nothing but still dress up

123
00:12:07,640 --> 00:12:09,640
just to fake being rich.

124
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:11,800
But when you go to Bangkok,

125
00:12:11,840 --> 00:12:14,360
you should try dressing
cool like me sometimes.

126
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:18,560
And seriously, stop driving
that old junk, it’s embarrassing.

127
00:12:21,920 --> 00:12:23,240
I don’t care.

128
00:12:23,400 --> 00:12:27,040
If anyone looks down on me for dressing simple
or driving a cheap car,

129
00:12:27,120 --> 00:12:29,120
people who judge others by appearances

130
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:31,200
aren’t good people anyway.

131
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:34,120
Damn... my bro is seriously the coolest.

132
00:12:34,120 --> 00:12:36,400
So slick. Come on, fist bump.

133
00:12:36,800 --> 00:12:38,760
That’s my bro right there.

134
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:41,160
- Go put those shirts away.
- Got it.

135
00:12:54,800 --> 00:12:56,960
Oh my, Miss Si.

136
00:12:57,120 --> 00:12:59,520
Did you buy another new car today?

137
00:12:59,520 --> 00:13:02,680
That’s three cars this month already.

138
00:13:02,720 --> 00:13:05,040
Well, I was in a bad mood, Auntie.

139
00:13:05,320 --> 00:13:08,400
And when I’m in a bad mood,
I go shopping and buy cars.

140
00:13:08,400 --> 00:13:09,960
You get it, right?

141
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:23,040
Come here, don’t open your eyes yet.

142
00:13:23,320 --> 00:13:25,680
Ready? If you’re ready...

143
00:13:25,720 --> 00:13:28,440
surprise!

144
00:13:30,320 --> 00:13:32,160
The car is so pretty, Dad.

145
00:13:32,160 --> 00:13:34,080
I want to drive it too.

146
00:13:34,320 --> 00:13:37,000
How about this…when you grow up,

147
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:39,160
Dad will buy you lots of cars, okay?

148
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:40,800
Promise, Dad?

149
00:13:40,840 --> 00:13:43,600
When I grow up, I’ll have lots of cars

150
00:13:43,640 --> 00:13:45,240
and I’ll drive you around.

151
00:13:45,280 --> 00:13:46,800
Promise.

152
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:49,000
Just driving Dad around?

153
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:51,560
- What about Mom?
- Mom too.

154
00:13:51,720 --> 00:13:53,480
Wherever you and Mom want to go,

155
00:13:53,520 --> 00:13:56,160
I’ll drive you everywhere.

156
00:13:57,800 --> 00:14:00,880
But Mom and Dad already have a driver.

157
00:14:00,920 --> 00:14:02,280
So how about this…

158
00:14:02,320 --> 00:14:05,960
you just sit pretty and be our princess, okay?

159
00:14:07,920 --> 00:14:09,560
Dad too, Dad too!

160
00:14:10,720 --> 00:14:15,480
- Come on, Your Highness, this way...
- This way, please...

161
00:14:15,800 --> 00:14:18,040
Alright, one moment please.

162
00:14:18,120 --> 00:14:19,280
Right this way.

163
00:14:19,280 --> 00:14:20,840
Thank you.

164
00:14:44,200 --> 00:14:45,880
The landowner said

165
00:14:45,920 --> 00:14:47,760
once the lease ends next year,

166
00:14:47,800 --> 00:14:50,280
they’ll turn it into an
agricultural learning center

167
00:14:50,320 --> 00:14:53,360
and use it as a rice farming demo field.

168
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:55,280
But I don’t think that’s true.

169
00:14:55,320 --> 00:14:57,120
No one’s crazy enough to use land

170
00:14:57,160 --> 00:14:58,840
in the middle of Bangkok for that.

171
00:15:01,920 --> 00:15:03,640
Hello, everyone.

172
00:15:09,720 --> 00:15:12,360
Let’s evaluate the budget first, okay?

173
00:15:12,400 --> 00:15:13,760
If we have to rebuild the mall,

174
00:15:13,920 --> 00:15:15,680
to match the current size

175
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:17,640
with today’s construction costs.

176
00:15:17,720 --> 00:15:19,840
At the very least, around twenty billion.

177
00:15:19,920 --> 00:15:21,640
As for the new location we’re considering,

178
00:15:21,640 --> 00:15:22,920
it can’t compare to the current one.

179
00:15:22,920 --> 00:15:24,680
It’s harder to access,

180
00:15:24,720 --> 00:15:27,760
and construction would
take at least three years.

181
00:15:27,800 --> 00:15:30,280
That means our business would be disrupted.

182
00:15:30,320 --> 00:15:32,720
There’s another party
offering a higher lease.

183
00:15:32,920 --> 00:15:36,120
Can we push our offer up a bit?

184
00:15:36,200 --> 00:15:38,920
The ceiling we set for negotiation

185
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:40,800
still stands at the same figure.

186
00:15:40,800 --> 00:15:42,240
Thirty percent.

187
00:15:42,320 --> 00:15:45,120
Anything higher would hurt the business.

188
00:15:45,320 --> 00:15:48,520
Let me add something
regarding the lease agreement.

189
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:51,560
Under the original contract
made by your grandfather

190
00:15:51,560 --> 00:15:53,400
with the current owner’s father,

191
00:15:53,400 --> 00:15:56,440
the owner has the right not to renew.

192
00:15:57,720 --> 00:16:00,160
We don’t have any leverage to force it.

193
00:16:00,320 --> 00:16:04,080
The old contract was very loose,
more like a friendly deal.

194
00:16:04,120 --> 00:16:05,400
And more importantly,

195
00:16:05,440 --> 00:16:07,640
the reason we need to decide quickly is...

196
00:16:07,920 --> 00:16:11,600
if we can’t reach an
agreement within this quarter,

197
00:16:11,600 --> 00:16:13,640
we’ll lose our bargaining power.

198
00:16:14,520 --> 00:16:16,200
We don’t have a choice in this game.

199
00:16:16,200 --> 00:16:17,960
We just have to win.

200
00:16:20,400 --> 00:16:23,800
Dad, does the air-con feel kinda warm today?

201
00:16:23,800 --> 00:16:25,200
Si!

202
00:16:25,320 --> 00:16:27,400
That’s totally inappropriate right now.

203
00:16:27,400 --> 00:16:31,640
Si, why don’t you go walk around
and shop at the mall first?

204
00:16:32,800 --> 00:16:35,560
No, Mom. I’m staying right here.

205
00:16:36,040 --> 00:16:38,840
P’Si, Dad’s really stressed right now.

206
00:16:38,920 --> 00:16:40,120
Hey, Song,

207
00:16:40,120 --> 00:16:41,760
I’m not dumb, okay?

208
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:43,800
I know exactly what everyone’s stressed about.

209
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:47,280
It’s kinda hot today,
I just wanna make the AC cooler.

210
00:16:47,320 --> 00:16:50,240
so everyone can cool down too, right?

211
00:16:50,920 --> 00:16:52,920
And don’t worry, everyone.

212
00:16:53,120 --> 00:16:55,360
About the lease negotiation,

213
00:16:55,400 --> 00:16:59,200
I’ll handle it myself and make it happen.

214
00:16:59,800 --> 00:17:01,520
Good, then don’t go anywhere.

215
00:17:01,520 --> 00:17:02,800
Show Dad what you’ve got.

216
00:17:02,800 --> 00:17:04,880
The landowner is on the way.

217
00:17:05,520 --> 00:17:06,760
Alright.

218
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:20,280
Hello, Klao.

219
00:17:20,319 --> 00:17:21,800
Please, this way to the meeting room.

220
00:17:21,800 --> 00:17:23,040
Everyone’s already here.

221
00:17:23,079 --> 00:17:26,560
- I prepared bael juice for you, your favorite.
- Thank you.

222
00:17:27,400 --> 00:17:28,840
This way, please.

223
00:17:45,320 --> 00:17:46,720
You’re here.

224
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:53,920
Where is she?

225
00:18:00,200 --> 00:18:01,800
Hey, you.

226
00:18:01,800 --> 00:18:03,600
Go get your boss. I’ll talk to her.

227
00:18:03,600 --> 00:18:05,680
I’m not trying to look down on you,

228
00:18:05,720 --> 00:18:08,000
but when I handle business deals,

229
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:10,000
I don’t waste time talking to subordinates.

230
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:13,760
Besides, talking to the boss
gets everything done in one go.

231
00:18:15,320 --> 00:18:17,920
I apologize on behalf of my sister.

232
00:18:18,120 --> 00:18:19,960
- This way, please.
- Hey, Song…

233
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:21,640
are you trying to embarrass me?

234
00:18:21,800 --> 00:18:24,320
I’m not trying to embarrass you, P’Si.

235
00:18:24,800 --> 00:18:25,880
Then you should

236
00:18:25,920 --> 00:18:28,400
learn to follow my lead sometimes.

237
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:31,480
You might not know this, but...

238
00:18:31,520 --> 00:18:34,000
in business negotiations,

239
00:18:34,040 --> 00:18:36,160
people don’t talk to subordinates. And also…

240
00:18:36,160 --> 00:18:38,920
talking to them won’t impress the boss anyway.

241
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:42,840
Small fry like that shouldn’t even
be sitting in our meeting room...

242
00:18:43,720 --> 00:18:44,960
Alright, P’Si.

243
00:18:45,120 --> 00:18:47,960
I’ll take your advice and learn from it.

244
00:18:48,400 --> 00:18:49,560
Good.

245
00:18:51,320 --> 00:18:52,480
Please.

246
00:18:52,880 --> 00:18:53,920
Song…

247
00:18:53,960 --> 00:18:57,520
I told you already, pleasing
subordinates don't work.

248
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:03,000
Yes, I understand now.

249
00:19:03,040 --> 00:19:06,200
Then go ask her to bring her boss in.

250
00:19:06,200 --> 00:19:08,680
So we don’t waste time…
everyone’s already waiting.

251
00:19:08,720 --> 00:19:10,480
Besides, it’s about time

252
00:19:10,520 --> 00:19:13,200
I show everyone what I can really do.

253
00:19:13,240 --> 00:19:15,200
Business negotiations for me?

254
00:19:15,200 --> 00:19:17,480
Easy.

255
00:19:18,520 --> 00:19:19,640
Of course, P’Si.

256
00:19:19,720 --> 00:19:21,960
Please, show us what you’ve got.

257
00:19:26,600 --> 00:19:28,400
Hey, you...

258
00:19:28,520 --> 00:19:30,680
Didn’t you hear a word I said?

259
00:19:30,720 --> 00:19:32,840
Go get your boss in here, now.

260
00:19:33,120 --> 00:19:34,240
Go on.

261
00:19:34,800 --> 00:19:35,960
P’Si...

262
00:19:36,600 --> 00:19:39,760
You’re already talking to Klao, the landowner.

263
00:19:46,040 --> 00:19:47,120
Oh, really?

264
00:19:53,320 --> 00:19:54,880
Hello.

265
00:20:02,960 --> 00:20:04,120
Deal.

266
00:20:06,080 --> 00:20:07,240
Are you serious?

267
00:20:07,280 --> 00:20:10,120
You’ll really renew the lease for us?

268
00:20:13,160 --> 00:20:14,960
I knew it.

269
00:20:14,960 --> 00:20:16,640
From the moment I saw you,

270
00:20:16,680 --> 00:20:18,040
I could tell,

271
00:20:18,080 --> 00:20:20,680
you’re a kind person.

272
00:20:20,680 --> 00:20:22,440
Is this what they call...

273
00:20:22,480 --> 00:20:23,640
a real one?

274
00:20:23,680 --> 00:20:24,720
Right?

275
00:20:24,760 --> 00:20:28,240
But I’m sure there’s a condition, isn’t there?

276
00:20:28,280 --> 00:20:30,000
What’s your condition?

277
00:20:30,160 --> 00:20:32,920
Hey, Song, can you not ruin this?

278
00:20:32,960 --> 00:20:35,400
She said she’ll sign, so she’ll sign.

279
00:20:35,480 --> 00:20:38,200
I’ve been negotiating this for three years,

280
00:20:38,240 --> 00:20:39,320
and still...

281
00:20:39,480 --> 00:20:41,800
I never got a clear answer.

282
00:20:42,160 --> 00:20:43,960
You should know by now

283
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:47,120
you and I aren’t on the same level.

284
00:20:47,360 --> 00:20:50,160
Don’t feel bad that I’m just better than you

285
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:53,520
and more suited to be the CEO.

286
00:20:55,360 --> 00:20:57,160
There has to be something else.

287
00:20:57,160 --> 00:20:59,400
Can you please tell us?

288
00:21:10,480 --> 00:21:13,120
I’m going to marry this woman.

289
00:21:27,480 --> 00:21:28,600
I...

290
00:21:30,680 --> 00:21:32,400
What do you mean?

291
00:21:33,960 --> 00:21:38,000
I’ll renew the land lease
for S Mall for another thirty years

292
00:21:38,040 --> 00:21:40,400
if I get to marry this woman.

293
00:21:52,560 --> 00:21:55,400
You mean my sister?

294
00:21:55,960 --> 00:21:57,120
Yes.

295
00:22:32,160 --> 00:22:34,080
My phone...

296
00:22:34,760 --> 00:22:36,000
P’Si...

297
00:22:36,600 --> 00:22:37,920
P’Si...

298
00:22:37,960 --> 00:22:39,240
I’m fine.

299
00:22:46,360 --> 00:22:49,000
Could we get, maybe,

300
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:51,120
another six months on the lease?

301
00:22:52,080 --> 00:22:55,200
Or... three months would work too.

302
00:22:55,560 --> 00:22:58,000
I don’t think that’s possible.

303
00:23:01,880 --> 00:23:04,080
Me? Marry you?

304
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:05,840
Are you out of your mind?

305
00:23:05,840 --> 00:23:07,840
Just because you won’t renew the lease

306
00:23:07,840 --> 00:23:10,560
and it might shut down my family’s mall,

307
00:23:10,560 --> 00:23:12,320
doesn’t mean we’ll go bankrupt

308
00:23:12,360 --> 00:23:14,120
and have nowhere to go, okay?

309
00:23:16,760 --> 00:23:17,840
Fine.

310
00:23:17,960 --> 00:23:19,040
If you

311
00:23:19,080 --> 00:23:20,240
change your mind,

312
00:23:20,280 --> 00:23:21,560
just give me a call.

313
00:23:21,560 --> 00:23:23,080
I’ll take my leave.

314
00:23:43,600 --> 00:23:44,680
What are you staring at?

315
00:24:14,760 --> 00:24:16,040
Hey, you,

316
00:24:16,080 --> 00:24:18,560
do you even realize what you just did

317
00:24:18,560 --> 00:24:20,880
was seriously rude?

318
00:24:24,360 --> 00:24:25,560
You,

319
00:24:26,560 --> 00:24:28,200
what are you doing?

320
00:24:29,680 --> 00:24:31,720
I wanted to know what you were listening to.

321
00:24:31,760 --> 00:24:33,560
I was saying something important,

322
00:24:33,600 --> 00:24:35,400
and you didn’t hear a thing.

323
00:24:39,760 --> 00:24:41,120
What song is that?

324
00:24:41,160 --> 00:24:42,600
So outdated.

325
00:24:43,880 --> 00:24:45,240
“Cucumber Garden Girl.”

326
00:24:45,280 --> 00:24:46,880
My favorite, actually.

327
00:24:47,080 --> 00:24:48,320
Outdated how?

328
00:24:48,560 --> 00:24:50,600
It’s classic.

329
00:24:57,160 --> 00:24:59,160
Anyway, you followed me out here,

330
00:24:59,160 --> 00:25:00,240
what do you want?

331
00:25:06,480 --> 00:25:08,600
About the marriage we talked about earlier in the meeting room.

332
00:25:09,600 --> 00:25:10,960
you were joking, right?

333
00:25:11,160 --> 00:25:13,200
We just met today.

334
00:25:13,360 --> 00:25:15,360
How can you bring me into this as a condition?

335
00:25:23,080 --> 00:25:24,520
What?

336
00:25:29,280 --> 00:25:30,520
Does my face

337
00:25:30,680 --> 00:25:32,680
look like I joke around?

338
00:25:39,360 --> 00:25:41,560
I don’t know, but what you did

339
00:25:41,600 --> 00:25:44,120
felt more like something
a crazy person would do.

340
00:25:49,880 --> 00:25:52,120
Hey, my earphones.

341
00:25:53,560 --> 00:25:55,520
Give them back.

342
00:26:00,160 --> 00:26:01,600
Is this your car?

343
00:26:02,080 --> 00:26:03,320
Yeah.

344
00:26:07,080 --> 00:26:08,640
A car like this...

345
00:26:08,640 --> 00:26:11,400
and you still park in the VVIP lot? Bold.

346
00:26:19,080 --> 00:26:20,720
Looking for something?

347
00:26:23,080 --> 00:26:25,320
This one?

348
00:26:37,880 --> 00:26:39,280
That’s my car key.

349
00:26:39,960 --> 00:26:41,520
How did you even get it?

350
00:26:42,200 --> 00:26:43,520
Give it back.

351
00:26:45,280 --> 00:26:46,440
Or you could...

352
00:26:46,480 --> 00:26:49,520
go back upstairs and talk
the contract through with me.

353
00:26:49,560 --> 00:26:51,320
Then I’ll return it.

354
00:26:53,080 --> 00:26:54,600
Oh, so we’re playing games now?

355
00:26:55,280 --> 00:26:57,440
What, you gonna hurt me?

356
00:26:57,480 --> 00:26:58,800
Or what exactly?

357
00:26:59,360 --> 00:27:01,280
This mall is mine.

358
00:27:01,280 --> 00:27:04,040
And all the security here work for me.

359
00:27:04,080 --> 00:27:06,600
Don’t even think about it.

360
00:27:15,160 --> 00:27:16,920
What are you going to do?

361
00:27:39,160 --> 00:27:41,000
Shocked, huh?

362
00:27:41,800 --> 00:27:42,880
I’m off then.

363
00:27:43,080 --> 00:27:44,200
Bye.

364
00:28:21,400 --> 00:28:24,040
From now on, you don’t need
to come into the company anymore.

365
00:28:24,080 --> 00:28:26,240
Every time you go in,
there’s always trouble.

366
00:28:26,560 --> 00:28:28,440
How can you stop me like this, Dad?

367
00:28:28,440 --> 00:28:30,200
I’m your daughter.

368
00:28:30,280 --> 00:28:32,320
I have every right to do anything.

369
00:28:32,360 --> 00:28:35,040
Weren’t you bragging you’d fix everything?

370
00:28:35,080 --> 00:28:36,640
You said you’d talk to the landowner,

371
00:28:36,680 --> 00:28:38,640
get them to renew the lease,
so what happened?

372
00:28:38,680 --> 00:28:40,480
It blew up in your face.

373
00:28:41,560 --> 00:28:43,600
Then I’ll marry her.

374
00:28:43,960 --> 00:28:46,520
So she’ll agree to renew the lease for us.

375
00:28:46,680 --> 00:28:48,080
Then you’ll finally be satisfied,

376
00:28:48,160 --> 00:28:50,200
and maybe you’ll actually see me for once.

377
00:28:50,280 --> 00:28:53,000
You’re really that naive?
You think she meant it?

378
00:28:53,160 --> 00:28:56,040
That kind of offer, anyone can tell

379
00:28:56,080 --> 00:28:58,160
no one would accept it.

380
00:28:58,280 --> 00:29:00,680
And you even went and insulted her.

381
00:29:00,960 --> 00:29:04,760
Everything we’ve built
is falling apart because of you.

382
00:29:06,960 --> 00:29:09,600
Calm down, please.
Can we talk about this later?

383
00:29:09,960 --> 00:29:11,000
Si.

384
00:29:12,280 --> 00:29:13,520
Go to your room first.

385
00:29:13,560 --> 00:29:14,640
No, Mom.

386
00:29:14,680 --> 00:29:15,840
I’m talking to Dad.

387
00:29:15,880 --> 00:29:18,240
Right now. Today.

388
00:29:18,880 --> 00:29:19,920
Si,

389
00:29:21,760 --> 00:29:23,120
Go to your room.

390
00:29:37,960 --> 00:29:39,280
P’Si...

391
00:29:39,800 --> 00:29:40,800
I mean...

392
00:29:41,760 --> 00:29:43,920
we can figure this out together.

393
00:31:02,200 --> 00:31:04,400
You freaking tapeworm.

394
00:31:18,680 --> 00:31:19,800
Hey.

395
00:31:21,760 --> 00:31:23,600
Where are the houses, huh?

396
00:31:23,960 --> 00:31:25,480
I don’t see a single one.

397
00:31:25,760 --> 00:31:27,120
We’ve been driving forever.

398
00:31:27,160 --> 00:31:28,840
If you wanna know,

399
00:31:28,840 --> 00:31:31,000
that’ll be another two hundred.

400
00:31:31,640 --> 00:31:35,320
- You little brat.
- Two hundred, two hundred.

401
00:31:35,360 --> 00:31:36,880
Are you trying to scam me?

402
00:31:37,280 --> 00:31:39,360
Aren’t you going to P’Klao’s house?

403
00:31:39,400 --> 00:31:43,080
I already paid you two hundred earlier.
What more do you want?

404
00:31:43,640 --> 00:31:46,720
Try that again
and I’ll report you to the police.

405
00:31:46,760 --> 00:31:49,280
Guys like you either sell or use.

406
00:31:50,240 --> 00:31:53,000
Oh really? That’s scary.

407
00:31:53,040 --> 00:31:58,400
Me? Never touched that stuff.
I’m clean, sweet as can be.

408
00:31:58,440 --> 00:32:00,200
- You little,
- You little,

409
00:32:00,240 --> 00:32:02,360
- You damn mutt tapeworm.
- Sis Nokkaew.

410
00:32:02,400 --> 00:32:03,680
My name’s not Nokkaew.

411
00:32:03,920 --> 00:32:06,600
Your cover’s got a parrot from
the headman’s house.

412
00:32:06,600 --> 00:32:08,680
That color’s loud.

413
00:32:08,720 --> 00:32:13,800
Looks like temple fair lights.
You’ve seen LED lights, right?

414
00:32:15,120 --> 00:32:16,840
You little,

415
00:32:16,880 --> 00:32:19,880
You little, you little,

416
00:32:22,440 --> 00:32:24,560
Breathing that hard?
Your sugar’s spiking.

417
00:32:24,560 --> 00:32:25,920
Got enough energy to slap me too?

418
00:32:25,960 --> 00:32:27,920
So, you paying the two hundred or not?

419
00:32:27,960 --> 00:32:29,960
I don’t have cash.

420
00:32:30,160 --> 00:32:32,520
Hey sis, look over there, up there.

421
00:32:32,560 --> 00:32:33,760
What?

422
00:32:35,840 --> 00:32:37,240
You little brat.

423
00:32:37,280 --> 00:32:38,840
I’ve got PromptPay, you know.

424
00:32:38,840 --> 00:32:40,880
I’m not some country bumpkin.

425
00:32:41,040 --> 00:32:43,120
Then stay still.

426
00:32:44,440 --> 00:32:46,880
- You want it or not?
- I want it.

427
00:32:47,360 --> 00:32:48,520
Hurry up, sis.

428
00:32:48,560 --> 00:32:50,520
Don’t let me see you again next time.

429
00:32:50,560 --> 00:32:52,160
- Then forget it.
- No, I want it!

430
00:32:55,960 --> 00:32:57,200
Here, take it.

431
00:32:57,240 --> 00:33:00,400
Now take me to the destination already.

432
00:33:01,360 --> 00:33:02,720
If you ditch me again,

433
00:33:02,760 --> 00:33:03,840
I swear I’ll kill you.

434
00:33:03,840 --> 00:33:07,520
Got it, sis. I’ll take you there nice and smooth.

435
00:33:07,560 --> 00:33:08,800
- Want me to open the door?
- No need.

436
00:33:08,840 --> 00:33:11,200
Can your ride even keep up, sis?

437
00:33:13,960 --> 00:33:16,280
Try and keep up with me.

438
00:33:23,360 --> 00:33:27,600
This morning, Khun Si asked me to send
a copy of the land lease.

439
00:33:27,640 --> 00:33:31,320
And also requested
Klao’s address and photos.

440
00:33:33,040 --> 00:33:36,000
What is P’Si planning to do?

441
00:33:40,240 --> 00:33:43,320
So this is the house I’ve been looking for?

442
00:33:44,360 --> 00:33:46,480
Why does this place look so creepy?

443
00:33:46,680 --> 00:33:48,360
Creepy? Come on, sis.

444
00:33:48,400 --> 00:33:49,720
This place is kinda cool.

445
00:33:49,760 --> 00:33:52,960
My bro’s got his own vibe. Real stylish.

446
00:33:52,960 --> 00:33:56,200
Ooh, someone’s impressed.

447
00:33:56,360 --> 00:33:58,800
So… you wanna meet P’Klao?

448
00:33:58,840 --> 00:34:01,640
Is she the same person I showed you?

449
00:34:01,640 --> 00:34:04,280
Yes, ma’am. One hundred percent match.

450
00:34:04,360 --> 00:34:06,800
Then where is she?

451
00:34:07,040 --> 00:34:09,400
She’s probably out in the fields by now.

452
00:34:09,400 --> 00:34:11,199
You’re kinda late.

453
00:34:11,239 --> 00:34:14,880
- The fields?
- Yep, rice fields. Out there.

454
00:34:19,960 --> 00:34:21,280
Then…

455
00:34:21,639 --> 00:34:23,719
go get her for me.

456
00:34:23,760 --> 00:34:25,320
Always happy to.

457
00:34:25,760 --> 00:34:28,320
- But it’s two hundred.
- Two hundred?

458
00:34:28,360 --> 00:34:29,360
Of course.

459
00:34:29,440 --> 00:34:30,880
You’re seriously money-hungry.

460
00:34:30,920 --> 00:34:32,320
Up to you, sis.

461
00:34:32,360 --> 00:34:35,199
- Go get her yourself then. I’m off.
- Wait, wait!

462
00:34:35,199 --> 00:34:36,800
Fine, I’ll pay.

463
00:34:39,239 --> 00:34:40,719
Here.

464
00:34:40,760 --> 00:34:42,239
I’ll give you extra this time.

465
00:34:42,280 --> 00:34:43,679
Four hundred.

466
00:34:44,159 --> 00:34:45,440
But go get her fast, okay?

467
00:34:45,440 --> 00:34:48,719
Thanks, sis. Got it, I’ll hurry.

468
00:34:48,760 --> 00:34:51,440
You’re looking prettier today, sis.
Thought you were some flashy parrot.

469
00:34:51,440 --> 00:34:53,120
Right this way, please.

470
00:34:53,159 --> 00:34:56,440
Have a seat, nice breeze.
Cool off a bit, sis.

471
00:34:56,440 --> 00:34:58,200
This way, please.

472
00:36:15,760 --> 00:36:16,800
Still staring?

473
00:36:16,960 --> 00:36:19,280
I just yelled at you and you’re still looking?

474
00:36:19,360 --> 00:36:20,720
Wanna get yourself
turned into fried chicken?

475
00:36:20,760 --> 00:36:22,720
I swear I’ll snap your neck.

476
00:36:28,920 --> 00:36:33,400
P’! P’! P’!

477
00:36:33,960 --> 00:36:35,120
P’!

478
00:36:35,160 --> 00:36:36,960
Someone’s here to see you.

479
00:36:37,000 --> 00:36:38,280
Not sure who.

480
00:36:38,440 --> 00:36:39,440
Who is it?

481
00:36:39,480 --> 00:36:41,400
No idea.

482
00:36:41,560 --> 00:36:43,480
But you can spot her from far away.

483
00:36:43,560 --> 00:36:45,880
Bright like a rainbow, seriously.

484
00:36:47,240 --> 00:36:48,480
Who the hell?

485
00:36:48,480 --> 00:36:51,480
Did you invite a girl over or something?

486
00:36:53,440 --> 00:36:55,880
Who knows what she’s carrying.

487
00:37:00,640 --> 00:37:03,400
You scared me. I thought you were a ghost.

488
00:37:05,440 --> 00:37:07,120
Took you long enough.

489
00:37:07,160 --> 00:37:08,680
Playing hard to get now?

490
00:37:08,760 --> 00:37:09,840
Hard to get?

491
00:37:09,960 --> 00:37:11,080
Who’s playing hard to get?

492
00:37:14,360 --> 00:37:16,800
Let’s talk inside. It’s too hot out here.

493
00:37:36,760 --> 00:37:38,200
What’s wrong?

494
00:37:39,280 --> 00:37:41,680
You should train that crazy chicken of yours.

495
00:37:43,080 --> 00:37:44,680
His name’s Jon.

496
00:37:44,840 --> 00:37:46,200
What did he do to you?

497
00:37:47,160 --> 00:37:48,920
He stared at me.

498
00:37:48,960 --> 00:37:51,760
And then he jumped at me just now.

499
00:37:54,640 --> 00:37:56,280
You really fought a chicken?

500
00:38:00,040 --> 00:38:01,880
I’ll go deal with him.

501
00:38:07,040 --> 00:38:08,560
Come sit here and wait.

502
00:38:08,840 --> 00:38:10,200
Hey, um,

503
00:38:10,960 --> 00:38:12,480
Can I get some water?

504
00:38:12,760 --> 00:38:14,400
It’s so hot.

505
00:39:47,960 --> 00:39:49,440
What kind of drink is this?

506
00:39:49,840 --> 00:39:51,280
Strawberry juice?

507
00:39:52,640 --> 00:39:54,600
You said you were thirsty, didn’t you?

508
00:39:55,840 --> 00:39:58,000
Don’t you have bottled water?

509
00:39:58,040 --> 00:39:59,840
I don’t usually drink from a dipper.

510
00:39:59,880 --> 00:40:01,680
I only drink mineral water.

511
00:40:02,960 --> 00:40:04,520
This is clean water.

512
00:40:04,640 --> 00:40:06,000
It’s boiled.

513
00:40:08,040 --> 00:40:10,600
Then why is it red?

514
00:40:10,840 --> 00:40:13,080
And jasmine flowers too?

515
00:40:13,360 --> 00:40:15,400
What if there’s pesticide in it?

516
00:40:17,360 --> 00:40:20,520
It’s red because I added Uthai water drops.

517
00:40:20,560 --> 00:40:22,760
It’ll refresh you.

518
00:40:23,040 --> 00:40:25,960
As for the jasmine, no need to worry.

519
00:40:25,960 --> 00:40:27,480
I grew it myself.

520
00:40:27,560 --> 00:40:29,720
Definitely no chemicals.

521
00:40:34,560 --> 00:40:35,920
On second thought…

522
00:40:35,960 --> 00:40:39,200
I’ll just go drink water at home.

523
00:40:39,440 --> 00:40:42,400
Well, if you’re not drinking,
you can leave then.

524
00:40:42,440 --> 00:40:45,200
That’s just rude.

525
00:40:47,760 --> 00:40:49,160
Okay.

526
00:40:49,560 --> 00:40:51,400
I’ll try it.

527
00:41:10,760 --> 00:41:12,120
I drank it.

528
00:41:12,360 --> 00:41:14,680
Can we talk business now?

529
00:41:30,640 --> 00:41:32,080
What are you doing?

530
00:41:35,120 --> 00:41:37,360
You’re such a messy eater, like a kid.

531
00:41:45,240 --> 00:41:47,560
So, how’s your leg?

532
00:41:50,640 --> 00:41:51,840
My leg?

533
00:41:52,600 --> 00:41:53,960
It’s pretty nice, actually.

534
00:41:54,000 --> 00:41:55,880
People always say my legs

535
00:41:55,920 --> 00:41:58,360
look like a model’s, right?

536
00:41:59,600 --> 00:42:01,440
Wow, you’re pretty full of yourself.

537
00:42:01,640 --> 00:42:02,880
I mean,

538
00:42:02,920 --> 00:42:04,960
how’s your fall from yesterday?

539
00:42:05,000 --> 00:42:06,880
I saw you limping.

540
00:42:06,920 --> 00:42:08,240
Does it still hurt?

541
00:42:11,720 --> 00:42:13,560
I’ve been driving a lot,

542
00:42:13,600 --> 00:42:15,240
so it’s just a bit sore.

543
00:42:17,720 --> 00:42:19,040
Here, put this on.

544
00:42:20,640 --> 00:42:23,960
It’s okay, I’ll just see a doctor in Bangkok.

545
00:42:39,320 --> 00:42:41,040
What kind of medicine is this?

546
00:42:41,200 --> 00:42:44,280
What if I use it and get a rash or an allergy?

547
00:42:44,320 --> 00:42:47,040
I’ll make you pay for laser treatment, you know.

548
00:42:48,200 --> 00:42:50,280
It’s a local OTOP product.

549
00:42:50,320 --> 00:42:52,400
The aunties here make it.

550
00:42:52,440 --> 00:42:54,320
Smells a bit strong, but…

551
00:42:54,640 --> 00:42:55,920
it works really well.

552
00:43:06,720 --> 00:43:09,320
What are you doing? I don’t let
people touch my feet like this.

553
00:43:09,320 --> 00:43:11,520
- Let go. I don’t like this.
- Stop yelling.

554
00:43:11,600 --> 00:43:13,720
I’ll have Jon come peck you, you know.

555
00:43:40,240 --> 00:43:41,560
What’s wrong?

556
00:43:41,600 --> 00:43:42,960
Your face is all red.

557
00:43:46,520 --> 00:43:48,440
It’s probably the heat.

558
00:43:51,000 --> 00:43:53,120
Then wanna talk under the house?

559
00:43:53,120 --> 00:43:54,440
There’s a fan inside.

560
00:43:57,320 --> 00:44:00,160
A fan… and ghosts too?

561
00:44:01,000 --> 00:44:03,040
This kind of house is creepy.

562
00:44:04,120 --> 00:44:06,440
What ghost would show up in broad daylight?

563
00:44:09,200 --> 00:44:10,320
But…

564
00:44:11,600 --> 00:44:13,440
at night, who knows.

565
00:44:19,200 --> 00:44:20,960
Wait up.

566
00:44:31,200 --> 00:44:32,960
You have a cat too?

567
00:44:37,320 --> 00:44:39,560
It’s so cute.

568
00:44:39,600 --> 00:44:41,400
What’s your name, baby?

569
00:44:41,400 --> 00:44:42,640
Her name’s Pao.

570
00:44:43,240 --> 00:44:44,360
Pao?

571
00:44:47,800 --> 00:44:50,960
So you’re scared of chickens but love cats?

572
00:44:51,800 --> 00:44:53,760
Well, she’s cute.

573
00:44:54,120 --> 00:44:57,600
I really wanted a cat when I was little,

574
00:44:57,600 --> 00:44:59,680
but my dad’s allergic to fur.

575
00:44:59,800 --> 00:45:01,360
So he wouldn’t let me.

576
00:45:02,600 --> 00:45:06,040
Well… if you like, you can come by more often.

577
00:45:15,120 --> 00:45:16,960
Why would I come here that often?

578
00:45:17,720 --> 00:45:20,760
I’m here for business.
Once is enough.

579
00:45:23,320 --> 00:45:25,240
Then go ahead.

580
00:45:26,920 --> 00:45:29,760
I came to talk about the lease.

581
00:45:30,680 --> 00:45:33,960
But I already told you everything I want.

582
00:45:34,600 --> 00:45:35,760
I know.

583
00:45:36,200 --> 00:45:38,360
That’s why I came all the way here.

584
00:45:38,400 --> 00:45:42,760
I’ve got a few… extra conditions.

585
00:45:45,600 --> 00:45:46,760
Let’s hear it.

586
00:45:58,600 --> 00:46:01,040
Bye-bye, Pao.

587
00:47:14,600 --> 00:47:17,160
Here’s Klao’s signature.

588
00:47:17,160 --> 00:47:18,960
I got it done for you, Dad.

589
00:47:19,000 --> 00:47:21,200
Boiled frogs, grilled rats,

590
00:47:21,200 --> 00:47:22,880
rice bowls.

591
00:47:23,280 --> 00:47:25,160
Who showers with the door open?

592
00:47:25,200 --> 00:47:27,160
I’m scared of ghosts, okay?

593
00:47:27,200 --> 00:47:28,640
Don’t look.

594
00:47:46,080 --> 00:47:47,080
(Jon, don’t be naughty)

595
00:47:54,360 --> 00:47:55,520
(Got you at last)

596
00:47:57,240 --> 00:47:59,960
If the workshop’s like this,
it’s super cute

597
00:48:00,000 --> 00:48:02,920
Hey hey, no chirping, okay?

598
00:48:02,960 --> 00:48:04,680
He won’t peck
(He won’t, right?) (Jon is gentle)

599
00:48:04,720 --> 00:48:06,760
No chirping, okay?

600
00:48:06,760 --> 00:48:08,560
(Thought you said no pecking)
It pecked me!

601
00:48:10,320 --> 00:48:11,760
(So cute I could squish you)

602
00:48:14,480 --> 00:48:16,480
(Good job, human)
